  "text": ". Products of this type are known not to exist for intersection homology. We will explain below why such products exist in the new theory but do not exist in intersection homology. Characteristic classes of pseudomanifolds, such as L-classes, lie generally in H * (X; Q), without possibility of lifting them to IH * (X; Q) or H * (IX; Q). Thus the value of the above product derives from the fact that it allows us to multiply Chern classes in H even (ImX; Q) of some bundle with the characteristic classes of X to obtain a class in the homology of InX. This may lead to extensions of the results of [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] on characteristic class formulae for twisted signatures and twisted L-classes of pseudomanifolds.",
